The paper focuses on improving the performance of deep models for fine-grained visual classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves weakly supervised learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of attention maps, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks.
